title Service Manager Lifecycle
' Registration · Lazy Initialization · Dependency Resolution · Retrieval

|Caller|
start
:call register(name, factory, options);

|ServiceManager|
:Yield one event-loop tick\n(setTimeout 0) — allows batch\nregistrations before processing;

|Factory|
:factory.create({ parameters, context })\n→ returns new service instance (ins);

|ServiceManager|
:Create entry = { name, instance: ins, status: **Registering** };
:Append to services_l_  •  Store in services_m_[name];

note right
  Entry is created and indexed.
  Status begins as **Registering**.
end note

:=== maybe_init_(name) ===;
:entry.instance.as(TService).get_depends() → depends[];
:get_waiting_for_(depends) → waiting_for[];

if (waiting_for[] is empty?) then (yes\nall deps Running)
  note right: All dependencies already Running.\nProceed directly to initialization.
else (no\nunresolved deps exist)
  :For each unresolved dep:\n  waiting_[dep].add(name);
  :Set entry.status = **Pending**;
  :Set entry.statusWaitingFor = waiting_for[];
  note right
    Service is deferred.
    Each pending dependency holds
    this service in waiting_[dep].
    Re-attempt fires when the last
    dependency reaches Running.
  end note
  :— suspended — awaiting dependency resolution —;
  :Dependency reaches Running →\ntriggers maybe_init_(name,\n{ no_init_listeners: true });
endif

:=== init_service_(name, modifiers) ===;
:Set entry.status = **Initializing**;
:service_impl = entry.instance.as(TService);

|TService|
:await service_impl.init();

|ServiceManager|
:Set entry.status = **Running**;
:Set entry.statusStartTS = new Date();

:Look up waiting_[name] → maybe_ready_set\n(services blocked on this one);

if (maybe_ready_set has blocked dependents?) then (yes)
  :For each blocked dependent:\n  push maybe_init_(dep,\n  { no_init_listeners: true });
  :await Promise.all(promises)\n[parallel cascade initialization];
  note right
    Cascade effect: resolving one service
    can unblock an entire chain of
    dependents via recursive maybe_init_.
  end note
endif

if (modifiers.no_init_listeners is falsy?) then (yes\nroot-level init)
  :For each listener in init_listeners_:\n  await listener();
  note right
    Notifies wait_for_init() and
    aget() promise waiters that a
    new service is now Running.
  end note
else (no\ncascade init)
  :Skip init_listeners_ notifications\n(suppress duplicate notifications\nduring dependency cascade);
endif

:Service is fully **Running** and available;

|Caller|
:Choose retrieval path;

|#DDEEFF|ServiceManager — get(name)|

:=== get(name) — synchronous retrieval ===;
:Look up info = services_m_[name];

if (info missing?) then (yes)
  :**throw** Error("Service not registered");
elseif (info.status ≠ Running?) then (yes)
  :Return **undefined**\n(registered but not yet Running);
else (Running)
  :Return **info.instance**;
endif

|#DDEEFF|ServiceManager — aget(name)|

:=== aget(name) — async-safe retrieval ===;
:await wait_for_init([name]);

:get_waiting_for_([name]) → still_waiting[];

if (still_waiting[] is empty?) then (yes\nalready Running)
  :Resolve Promise immediately;
else (no\nnot yet Running)
  :Register check() in init_listeners_;
  note right
    Push-listener pattern — no polling.
    check() is called by init_service_
    each time a service reaches Running.
  end note
  :Suspend — await init_service_ to fire listeners;
  :check() invoked → re-call get_waiting_for_();
  :Remove check() from init_listeners_;
  :Resolve Promise;
endif

:call get(name) → return **info.instance**;

|Caller|
:Receive service instance;
stop

@enduml
